    ("How does GRACE score guide ACS management?", "GRACE in-hospital mortality: Low (<108): <1%. Intermediate (108–140): 1–3%. High (>140): >3%. For NSTEMI: high GRACE score (>140) indicates benefit from early invasive strategy (coronary angiography within 24 hours). Low GRACE score allows selective invasive approach. STEMI patients proceed to primary PCI regardless of GRACE score."),
